article.headline: Austin Peay 78, Middle Tennessee 75
article.story: MURFREESBORO, Tenn. (AP) -- Drake Reed led three other players in double figures Saturday night to help Austin Peay beat Middle Tennessee 78-75. Reed had 17 points, while Derek Wright scored 16, West Channels added 11, and Ernest Fields contributed 10. Middle Tennessee (4-8) led 37-35 at the half. But Austin Peay (7-6) opened the second half with a 9-0 run to go up 45-37. The Blue Raiders later tied the game at 69-69 on a free throw by Green with 2:05 left to play. But the Governors took the lead for good minutes later on a jumper by Channels. Middle Tennessee shot 50 percent from the field, compared to 41 percent for Austin Peay. But the Blue Raiders were 18-for-27 from the free throw line, compared to 31-for-36 for the Governors.
